- feature_id 0 refers to the 'Login Module'; 
- The query ranks test cases in descending order of average execution time, implying that a higher rank indicates a longer average execution time; 
- The results are limited to the top 3 test cases for each tester; 
- The purpose is to identify the most time-consuming test cases for the Login Module and associate them with the corresponding testers.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(test_case_id) AS unexecuted_test_cases
FROM test_cases
WHERE test_case_id NOT IN (SELECT test_case_id FROM test_runs);

SELECT tester_name, role
FROM testers
ORDER BY tester_name ASC;

